1. Install [Homebrew](https://brew.sh/)
```sh
/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"
```

```sh
brew analytics off
```

2. Install [chessx](https://chessx.sourceforge.io/) and the [stockfish engine](https://stockfishchess.org)
```sh
brew install --cask chessx
```
```sh
brew install stockfish
```

3. Create a finder alias from following path on your desktop: `/usr/local/Cellar/stockfish/`

4. Launch chessx and go into the preferences

5. Hit `Reset`

6. Now go to the preferences tab named `Engines` (in ğŸ‡©ğŸ‡ª: `Schachprogramme`)

7. Add the stockfish executable with the finder alias you've created in step _3_

8. Now you should be able to run analyzes for your chess matches with stockfish in chessx

